+{"id":"franken_networkx-codprop-review","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: diameter/radius graph-property contracts diverge","description":"The cod graph-properties conformance matrix found diameter and radius diverge from upstream NetworkX on empty graphs and directed strongly connected cycles. Empty Graph: fnx raises NetworkXPointlessConcept while nx raises ValueError('max() arg is an empty sequence'). Directed 3-cycle: fnx returns diameter/radius 1 while nx returns 2 because directed distances are respected.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-codtrav-review","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: topological_sort tie-break order diverges from NetworkX","description":"The cod traversal conformance matrix found topological_sort on a diamond DAG with insertion order [('s','a'), ('s','b'), ('a','c'), ('b','c')] returns ['s','b','a','c'] in fnx while upstream NetworkX returns ['s','a','b','c']. The output is a valid topological order but diverges from NetworkX-observable insertion-order tie policy.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-codrgen-review","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: seeded random generator outputs diverge from NetworkX","description":"The cod random-generator conformance matrix found seeded watts_strogatz_graph(12,4,0.3,seed=5) and barabasi_albert_graph(10,2,seed=5) produce graphs with different edge sets from upstream NetworkX. Seeded exact-output parity is required for drop-in reproducibility.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-evdvlst", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] EdgeView(data=\"attr\") keys() yields 3-tuples \u2014 dict() silently corrupts", "description": "fnx.Graph.edges(data=\"w\") returned the raw EdgeView with keys() + __getitem__ attached. dict(G.edges(data=\"w\")) used the keys path and produced {(u, v, val): {w: val}} \u2014 3-tuple keys mapped to attrs dicts. nx raises ValueError on dict(G.edges(data=...)) because its EdgeDataView has no keys(). Fix: materialize edges(data=non-False) into a plain list in _edge_view_call_with_nbunch_first so dict() sees tuples-only and matches nx contract.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T05:42:30.531433Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-4 cycle-2: _edge_view_call_with_nbunch_first now returns list() when data is non-False. Both fnx and nx now raise the same ValueError on dict(G.edges(data=\"w\")).", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T05:42:30.531433Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T05:42:30.531433Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-privadj", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] fnx graphs missing private _adj/_node/_succ/_pred aliases \u2014 nx internals crash", "description": "nx algorithms frequently reach into G._adj / G._node / G._succ / G._pred dict storage directly (e.g. connected_components._plain_bfs, bipartite.is_bipartite_node_set, link_prediction helpers). fnx graph classes exposed only the public adj/nodes/succ/pred views but none of the private underscore-prefixed aliases, so nxb.is_bipartite_node_set(fnx_graph, ns) crashed with AttributeError: franken_networkx.Graph object has no attribute _adj. Fix: add property aliases mapping _adj -> adj, _node -> nodes, _succ -> succ, _pred -> pred on all 4 graph classes. Read paths through these aliases hit the existing AdjacencyView / NodeView wrappers.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T05:47:29.541130Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-4 cycle-2: Graph/DiGraph/MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph now expose _adj, _node, (+ _succ, _pred on directed) as property aliases for the public views. Regression tests cover bipartite + connected_components via nx on fnx graphs.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T05:47:29.541130Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T05:47:29.541130Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
